    "heading_text": "Forbid Extra Headers",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/header-param-models/#forbid-extra-headers",
    "chunk_index": 0,
    "chunk_text": "Forbid Extra Headers. In some special use cases (probably not very common), you might want to restrict the headers that you want to receive. You can use Pydantic's model configuration to forbid any extra fields: If a client tries to send some extra headers , they will receive an error response. For example, if the client tries to send a tool header with a value of plumbus , they will receive an error response telling them that the header parameter tool is not allowed:",
