    "heading_text": "Disable Convert Underscores",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/header-param-models/#disable-convert-underscores",
    "chunk_index": 0,
    "chunk_text": "Disable Convert Underscores. The same way as with regular header parameters, when you have underscore characters in the parameter names, they are automatically converted to hyphens . For example, if you have a header parameter save_data in the code, the expected HTTP header will be save-data , and it will show up like that in the docs. If for some reason you need to disable this automatic conversion, you can do it as well for Pydantic models for header parameters.",
